  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "A large oil painting on canvas by **Isaac Israëls** (Amsterdam, 1865 – The Hague, 1934), depicting a North African woman in loose-fitting attire beating a drum before a Parisian fairground wrestling tent. Painted during Israëls' Paris period (c. 1904–1913), the painting shows a drummer performing the role of street \"barker\" to attract spectators to a sideshow. A poster of wrestlers is visible on the wall behind her. The Teylers version (KS 165) is one of at least four known versions of this composition by Israëls; the Rijksmuseum holds a closely related work (SK-C-983). Designated one of Teylers' **50 Topstukken**.",
